dc_title_s: The Antilles or West-India islands / J. & C. Walker, sculpt. [copy 1]
dc_description_s: Map of the West Indies islands, also known as the Greater Antilles Islands, showing the distribution of the islands among six nationalities - the British, the French, the Spanish, the Dutch, the Swedish and the Danish. The size and population of each island is also listed. Relief is shown by hachures on the three central islands of the Antilles. Imprint on map: Published Jany. 1st, 1835 by Baldwin & Cradock, 47 Paternoster Row, London. Map 73 from: A series of maps, modern and ancient, under the superintendence of the Society for the Diffusion of Useful Knowledge. London : Baldwin & Cradock, [1829-35].
